FBIS4-35781 "drnes107_n_94001" FBIS-NES-94-107 Daily Report 2 Jun 1994 LEBANON Israeli Overflights, Shelling Continue in South Israeli Overflights, Shelling Continue in South Army Declares State of Alert NC0206155794 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1530 GMT 2 Jun 94 NC0206155794 Beirut Radio Lebanon Arabic BFN [Text] The Army command has declared a state of alert among all its units in Lebanon to confront any possibility of an Israeli escalation. This Army step comes in response to an Israeli military source's statement that the occupation forces have been placed on a maximum state of alert along the borders with Lebanon as a precaution against any fierce reprisals by Hizballah.
